WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.108
{"en":"--- lesson 33  A day to remember ","ch":"难忘的一天 "}

2
00:00:04.258 --> 00:00:08.523
{"en":"We have all experienced days when everything goes wrong. ^ ","ch":"我们大家都有过事事不顺心的日子。  "}

3
00:00:08.673 --> 00:00:14.635
{"en":"A day may begin well enough,  but suddenly everything seems to get out of control. ^ ","ch":"一天开始时， 可能还不错， 但突然间似乎一切都失去了控制。  "}

4
00:00:14.785 --> 00:00:22.707
{"en":"What invariably happens is that a great number of things choose to go wrong at precisely the same moment. ^ ","ch":"情况经常是这样的， 许许多多的事情都偏偏赶在同一时刻出问题，  "}

5
00:00:22.857 --> 00:00:28.480
{"en":"It is as if a single unimportant event set up a chain of reactions. ^ ","ch":"好像是一件无关紧要的小事引起了一连串的连锁反应。  "}

6
00:00:28.630 --> 00:00:35.742
{"en":"Let us suppose that you are preparing a meal and keeping an eye on the baby at the same time. ^ ","ch":"假设你在做饭， 同时又在照看孩子。  "}

7
00:00:35.892 --> 00:00:43.579
{"en":"The telephone rings and this marks the prelude to an unforeseen series of catastrophes. ^ ","ch":"这时电话铃响了。 它预示着一连串意想不到的灾难的来临。  "}

8
00:00:43.729 --> 00:00:49.195
{"en":"While you are on the phone,  the baby pulls the tablecloth off the table, ^ ","ch":"就在你接电话时， 孩子把桌布从桌子上扯下来，  "}

9
00:00:49.345 --> 00:00:54.629
{"en":"smashing half your best crockery and cutting himself in the process. ^ ","ch":"将家中最好的陶瓷餐具半数摔碎， 同时也弄伤了他自己。  "}

10
00:00:54.779 --> 00:01:00.062
{"en":"You hang up hurriedly and attend to baby,  crockery,  etc. ^ ","ch":"你急急忙忙挂上电话， 赶去照看孩子和餐具。  "}

11
00:01:00.212 --> 00:01:02.883
{"en":"Meanwhile,  the meal gets burnt. ^ ","ch":"这时， 饭又烧糊了。  "}

12
00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:12.157
{"en":"As if this were not enough to reduce you to tears,  your husband arrives,  unexpectedly bringing three guests to dinner. ^ ","ch":"好像这一切还不足以使你急得掉泪， 你的丈夫接着回来了， 事先没打招呼就带来3个客人吃饭。  "}

13
00:01:12.307 --> 00:01:21.195
{"en":"Things can go wrong on a big scale,  as a number of people recently discovered in Parramatta,  a suburb of Sydney. ^ ","ch":"就像许多人最近在悉尼郊区帕拉马塔所发现的那样， 有时乱子会闹得很大。  "}

14
00:01:21.345 --> 00:01:28.588
{"en":"During the rush hour one evening two cars collided and both drivers began to argue. ^ ","ch":"一天傍晚交通最拥挤时， 一辆汽车撞上前面一辆汽车， 两个司机争吵起来。  "}

15
00:01:28.738 --> 00:01:33.865
{"en":"The woman immediately behind the two cars happened to be a learner. ^ ","ch":"紧跟其后的一辆车上的司机碰巧是个初学者，  "}

16
00:01:34.015 --> 00:01:38.541
{"en":"She suddenly got into a panic and stopped her car. ^ ","ch":"她一惊之下突然把车停了下来。  "}

17
00:01:38.691 --> 00:01:42.433
{"en":"This made the driver following her brake hard. ^ ","ch":"她这一停使得跟在后头的司机也来个急刹车。  "}

18
00:01:42.583 --> 00:01:46.717
{"en":"His wife was sitting beside him holding a large cake. ^ ","ch":"司机妻子正坐在他身边， 手里托着块大蛋糕。  "}

19
00:01:46.867 --> 00:01:53.953
{"en":"As she was thrown forward,  the cake went right through the windscreen and landed on the road. ^ ","ch":"她往前一冲， 蛋糕从挡风玻璃飞了出去掉到马路上。 此时， 一辆卡车正好从后边开到那辆汽车边上，  "}

20
00:01:54.103 --> 00:02:03.644
{"en":"Seeing a cake flying through the air,  a lorry driver who was drawing up alongside the car,  pulled up all of a sudden. ^ ","ch":"司机看见一块蛋糕从天而降， 紧急刹车。  "}

21
00:02:03.794 --> 00:02:12.944
{"en":"The lorry was loaded with empty beer bottles and hundreds of them slid off the back of the vehicle and on to the road. ^ ","ch":"卡车上装着空啤酒瓶。 成百只瓶子顺势从卡车后面滑出车外落在马路上。  "}

22
00:02:13.094 --> 00:02:17.150
{"en":"This led to yet another angry argument. ^ ","ch":"这又引起了一场唇枪舌剑的争吵。  "}

23
00:02:17.300 --> 00:02:20.833
{"en":"Meanwhile,  the traffic piled up behind. ^ ","ch":"与此同时， 后面的车辆排成了长龙，  "}

24
00:02:20.983 --> 00:02:26.397
{"en":"It took the police nearly an hour to get the traffic on the move again. ^ ","ch":"警察花了将近一个小时才使车辆又开起来。  "}

25
00:02:26.547 --> 00:02:32.980
{"en":"In the meantime,  the lorry driver had to sweep up hundreds of broken bottles. ^ ","ch":"在这段时间里， 卡车司机不得不清扫那几百只破瓶子。  "}

26
00:02:33.130 --> 00:02:41.679
{"en":"Only two stray dogs benefited from all this confusion,  for they greedily devoured what was left of the cake. ^ ","ch":"只有两只野狗从这一片混乱中得到了好处， 它们贪婪地吃掉了剩下的蛋糕。  "}

27
00:02:41.829 --> 00:02:44.970
{"en":"It was just one of those days! ^ ","ch":"这就是事事不顺心的那么一天！  "}

